e-local navigation surface with a close button that calls `navController.navigateUp()`, and it keeps the cart sections inside one scrollable screen instead of exposing drawer or tab navigation.\",\n657:           \"Cart observes `viewModel.cartState` and immediately recomposes the item list when the snapshot changes, while note text stays local to the cart item section.\",\n658:           \"Cart updates system-bar colors and composes cart sections, but it does not request runtime permissions, handle permission callbacks, or call protected Android APIs.\",\n659:           \"Cart performs route-entry setup by collecting the current cart snapshot from `CartViewModel`, applying cart-specific window styling, and rendering the cart sections from that route-local state.\",\n660:           \"CartViewModel exposes observable cart state from repository flow collection so the cart route can render from the latest snapshot and filter visible items in UI.\",\n661:           \"CartViewModel collects cart items from the repository only; it does not request permissions, process permission results, or access protected APIs.\",\n662:           \"CartViewModel performs cart-screen initialization in `init` by starting collection of `userDataRepository.getCartItems()` so the cart snapshot is ready as soon as the screen observes it.\"\n663:         ],\n664:         \"riskHints\": [\n665:           \"critical/high behavior cannot close on build pass alone\"\n666:         ],\n667:         \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n668:           \"Closed critical/high features must record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence.\",\n669:           \"Build pass alone is not per-feature verification.\",\n670:           \"Referenced target tests are not strong evidence until a latest test gate PASS or explicit harness blocker is recorded.\"\n671:         ],\n672:         \"architectureHints\": [\n673:           \"If several source files are merged, keep business